description:
I whipped this up quickly after not finding any other styles that gave the results I wanted. This theme was made for the Elementary theme for Firefox on Ubuntu. I cannot guarantee results on other operating systems or with other themes. In fact, I'm fairly certain it'd look horrible with any other themes. :P

It was inspired by style 13511 by user 14809. I admit that I referenced his code in order to figure out what everything did, as this is the first style I've ever made. I kept the code simple as I don't think I could do much else. If I can figure it out, I'll try to get some subtle gradients in the tabs later, and maybe tweak the borders a bit. Feel free to leave suggestions and tips!

//UPDATES
- Added highlight on mouse-over to unselected tabs
- Gave active tab a gradient

//MORE UPDATES
- Tab strip and inactive tabs now have gradient backgrounds. Probably won't update it any more beyond this unless the Elementary theme changes significantly.

//YET MORE UPDATES
A user on the Elementary Project forums created a modified version of this theme for the Tabs-on-Top extension for Firefox. It's really nice and I recommend checking it out! http://www.elementary-project.com/forum/viewtopic.php?p=177#p177

css:
/* Created by Ramsey G. 02/2010; inspired by "Upside-Down Tabs [Safari-tabs]" by xren */

/* Note that this was only tested in Ubuntu Karmic with the Elementary Theme. I cannot guarantee good results in other configurations, but I'll try. */

@namespace url(http://www.mozilla.org/keymaster/gatekeeper/there.is.only.xul);

.tabbrowser-strip {
      background: url("data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAAeCAYAAADtlXTHAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAADxJREFUCNddzkEKw1AAAtE33v9c/1rpojQN2YjoIDrnXBNbGRksWbGWqWcG06wvzOyP/OQ15VXcTt0P+AAKLwPCDwaCEgAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==") !important; }

.tabbrowser-tab {
      -moz-appearance: none !important;
      background: #ececec url("data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAAeCAYAAADtlXTHAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAACBJREFUCNdjePv27X+m////MzAxMDAwQFj4CSLUUWoUADNeTrYWgqEgAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC") !important;
      border-left: 1px solid !important;
      border-right: 1px solid !important;
      border-bottom: 1px solid !important;
      border-top: none !important;
      -moz-border-left-colors: ThreeDShadow !important;
      -moz-border-right-colors: ThreeDShadow !important;
      -moz-border-bottom-colors: ThreeDShadow !important;
      -moz-border-radius-topleft: 0 !important;
      -moz-border-radius-topright: 0 !important;
      -moz-border-radius-bottomleft: 6px !important;
      -moz-border-radius-bottomright: 6px !important;
      margin: 0 1px 2px 0 !important; }

.tabbrowser-tab:not([selected="true"]) {
      background: #bebebe url("data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAAaCAYAAAB2BDbRAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAADpJREFUCNddjcEJxEAAhGT672+70TyyEO5+A4rDOadFLGMAq5jJMGaw8oJPSZlw1x81b/SV+/mwWMQDgzM8bq4r41QAAAAASUVORK5CYII=") !important;
      margin: 0 1px 4px 0 !important; }

.tabbrowser-tab:not([selected="true"]):hover {
      background: #dedede !important; }
